description.p:
According to a first aspect of embodiments of the present disclosure, there is provided a method of binding a token key to an account, comprising:
sending a binding request message carrying an account to a server, so that the server generates a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account;
acquiring the certification link and the first token key, and generating display information according to the certification link and the first token key, so that a mobile terminal obtains encrypted information according to the first token key, and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information, and further so that the server receives the access request message, and sends the encrypted information;
acquiring the encrypted information, and obtaining a second token key according to the encrypted information; and
sending a binding success message to the server after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key, so that the server binds the first token key to the account.

According to a second aspect of the embodiments of the present disclosure, there is provided a method of binding a token key to an account, comprising:
receiving a binding request message carrying an account sent at a webpage side;
generating a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account, so that the webpage side generates display information according to the certification link and the first token key, and further so that a mobile terminal obtains encrypted information according to the first token key, and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information;
receiving the access request message, and sending the encrypted information, so that the webpage side obtains a second token key according to the encrypted information, and sends a binding success message after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key; and
receiving the binding success message, and binding the first token key to the account.

According to a fourth aspect of the embodiments of the present disclosure, there is provided an apparatus for binding an account and a token key, comprising:
a first sending module configured to send a binding request message carrying an account to a server, so that the server generates a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account;
a first acquisition module configured to acquire the certification link and the first token key;
a first generation module configured to generate display information according to the certification link and the first token key, so that a mobile terminal obtains encrypted information according to the first token key, and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information, and further so that the server receives the access request message, and sends the encrypted information;
a second acquisition module configured to acquire the encrypted information;
a second generation module configured to obtain a second token key according to the encrypted information; and
a second sending module configured to send a binding success message to the server after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key, so that the server binds the first token key to the account.

According to a fifth aspect of the embodiments of the present disclosure, there is provided an apparatus of binding a token key to an account, comprising:
a first receiving module configured to receive a binding request message carrying an account sent at a webpage side;
a generation module configured to generate a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account, so that the webpage side generates display information according to the certification link and the first token key, and further so that a mobile terminal obtains encrypted information according to the first token key, and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information;
a second receiving module configured to receive the access request message;
a sending module configured to send the encrypted information, so that the webpage side obtains a second token key according to the encrypted information, and sends a binding success message after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key;
a third receiving module configured to receive the binding success message; and
a binding module configured to bind the first token key to the account.
In conjunction with the fifth aspect, in a first possible implementation manner of the fifth aspect, the apparatus further comprises:
an establishing module configured to establish a communication connection with the webpage side; and
a releasing module configured to release the communication connection with the webpage side if the access request message sent by the mobile terminal is not received in a setting period.

