claim.claim-text:
A method of binding a token key to an account, characterized by comprising:
a webpage sending a binding request message carrying an account to a server, so that the server generates a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account;
the webpage acquiring the certification link and the first token key, and generating display information according to the certification link and the first token key, so that an electronic device obtains encrypted information according to the first token key and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information to the server and the server receiving the access request message and sending the encrypted information to the electronic device;
the electronic device acquiring the encrypted information, and obtaining a second token key according to the encrypted information; and
the electronic device sending a binding success message to the server after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key, and the server binding the first token key to the account.

A method of binding a token key to an account, which is applied at a server, characterized by comprising:
the server receiving a binding request message carrying an account sent from a webpage;
the server generating a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account, so that the webpage generates display information according to the certification link and the first token key, and further so that an electronic device obtains encrypted information according to the first token key and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information;
the server receiving the access request message, and sending the encrypted information, so that the webpage obtains a second token key according to the encrypted information and sends a binding success message after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key; and
the server receiving the binding success message, and binding the first token key to the account.

An apparatus of binding a token key to an account, characterized by comprising:
a first sending module configured to send a binding request message carrying an account to a server, so that the server generates a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account;
a first acquisition module configured to acquire the certification link and the first token key;
a first generation module configured to generate display information according to the certification link and the first token key, so that an electronic device obtains encrypted information according to the first token key and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information, and further so that the server receives the access request message and sends the encrypted information;
a second acquisition module configured to acquire the encrypted information;
a second generation module configured to obtain a second token key according to the encrypted information; and
a second sending module configured to send a binding success message to the server after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key, so that the server binds the first token key to the account.

An apparatus for binding an account and a token key, characterized by comprising:
a first receiving module configured to receive a binding request message carrying an account sent by a webpage;
a generation module configured to generate a certification link and a first token key corresponding to the account, so that the webpage generates display information according to the certification link and the first token key, and further so that an electronic device obtains encrypted information according to the first token key, and sends an access request message carrying the certification link and the encrypted information;
a second receiving module configured to receive the access request message;
a sending module configured to send the encrypted information, so that the webpage obtains a second token key according to the encrypted information, and sends a binding success message after determining the second token key is consistent with the first token key;
a third receiving module configured to receive the binding success message; and
a binding module configured to bind the first token key to the account.
